## [Voyant Tools with Middlemarch Text](https://voyant-tools.org/?corpus=6d0403ca077682d7ec2419f59f091f84)

For this post, I tried to analyze Middlemarch with Voyant Tools. I chose Middlemarch because I am reading it for class right now, and because it is quite a long novel, which means that there is plenty of text to analyze. I used the text from project Guttenberg, which seemed to work quite well. Voyant has a few interesting ways of analyzing the text. The most eye-catching of these is the word cloud. When I first entered the text, the words "said" and "mr" dominated the word cloud, so I added them to the stopwords list that Voyant has pre-loaded because they did not seem to add anything substantial my understanding of the text.
